%% Diagram: JWT validation at the gateway with cached JWKS
%% Type: sequence
%%{init: {'htmlLabels': false}}%%
sequenceDiagram
    participant Client
    participant Gateway as API Gateway
    participant JWKS as IdP JWKS Endpoint
    participant Backend

    Client->>Gateway: HTTPS request + Authorization Bearer JWT
    Note over Gateway: Decode header, read kid
    alt kid in local cache
        Note over Gateway: Use cached public key
    else kid unknown (key rotation)
        Gateway->>JWKS: GET /.well-known/jwks.json
        JWKS-->>Gateway: JWK set (Cache-Control max-age)
        Note over Gateway: Update cache, retry verify
    end
    Note over Gateway: Verify signature, exp, iss, aud, nbf
    alt Token valid
        Gateway->>Backend: Forward request + claims headers
        Backend-->>Gateway: 200 OK
        Gateway-->>Client: 200 OK
    else Token invalid or expired
        Gateway-->>Client: 401 Unauthorized
    end
